#: ../../source/omjulia.rst:2
msgid "OMJulia – OpenModelica Julia Scripting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omjulia.rst:4
msgid ""
"OMJulia – the OpenModelica Julia API is a free, open source, highly "
"portable Julia based interactive session handler for Julia scripting of "
"OpenModelica API functionality. It provides the modeler with components "
"for creating a complete Julia-Modelica modeling, compilation and "
"simulation environment based on the latest OpenModelica implementation "
"and Modelica library standard available. OMJulia is architectured to "
"combine both the solving strategy and model building. Thus, domain "
"experts (people writing the models) and computational engineers (people "
"writing the solver code) can work on one unified tool that is "
"industrially viable for optimization of Modelica models, while offering a"
" flexible platform for algorithm development and research. OMJulia is not"
" a standalone package, it depends upon the OpenModelica installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omjulia.rst:18
msgid ""
"OMJulia is implemented in Julia and depends on ZeroMQ - high performance "
"asynchronous messaging library and it supports the Modelica Standard "
"Library version 3.2 that is included in starting with OpenModelica 1.9.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omjulia.rst:23
msgid ""
"To install OMJulia follow the instructions at "
"https://github.com/OpenModelica/OMJulia.jl"
msgstr ""

